parties.title: WWDC19 WeWork Labs Founders Happy Hour
parties.details: As a partner to entrepreneurs all over the world, WeWork Labs empowers early-stage startups to put their vision in motion through a tailored approach to mentorship, programming, community building, and innovation. Join us to learn more about the program and meet our team over great conversation, food and drinks!

parties.title: Micro.blog WWDC Meetup 2019
parties.details:
We are organizing the 3rd Annual Micro.blog meetup during WWDC week in San Jose for anyone interested in Micro.blog. Meet Manton, Jean, and other microbloggers. Ask questions and share tips.

When: Tuesday, June 4, 12 - 2 pm.
Where: outside Grace Deli, 303 S. Almaden Blvd. (Across from the Hilton)

Please let us know if you are interested in coming so we can stake out the tables and chairs outdoors. We also need to know how many stickers to bring! There's plenty of space. It's been a fun casual get-together the last two years, so we are looking forward to it.

parties.title: Nami ML Party @ WWDC 2019
parties.details: From the founders of Push IO, Dan & Joe have been in stealth working on something new... Be the first to see what we've been working on, an entirely new platform to help app developers.

parties.title: Night of Dim Sum 2019
parties.details: Join us for a night of all-you-can-eat dim sum! Located just a couple of miles from downtown San Jose in the Westfield Valley Fair Mall (where there is also an Apple Store and a LEGO store), Din Tai Fung is internationally known as one of the world's best Shanghai dumpling restaurants.

parties.title: HomeKit Meetup
parties.details:
Are you a developer working on HomeKit hardware, firmware, or apps? Maybe just a user who is interested in HomeKit. We are getting folks together in San Jose to hang out and have a beer and talk smart home. We will meet up outside in the back of Original Gravity Public House around 9 for about an hour, they close at 10PM on Tuesdays. If folks want to continue we can find another bar to go to afterwords.

Adam & Leo from ConnectSense will have some stickers, pins and other swag to hand out. If you want to bring something to share with the group feel free.

parties.title: WWDC Breakfast Burritos with Embrace!
parties.details:
Complimentary breakfast burritos served to hungry attendees of WWDC & AltConf!

To help fuel developers through the many sessions, meetups, conferences and happy hours during the week of WWDC, Embrace is serving free breakfast burritos for the iOS community!

On the mornings of June 4th and 5th, the Embrace team will be parked near the convention center handing out breakfast burritos for hungry attendees of WWDC and AltConf.
